{
  "texts": [
    "We experiment with the three training scenarios described previously.",
    "All models are trained on the original training split provided by the task organisers, using either data in all 6 seen languages; all EN data and the translations into English of the data in the other 5 languages; or only using the EN part of the training data.",
    "Each model is then evaluated on the task organiser's test split (6 seen and 3 surprise languages), without translation.",
    "Aligned with previous research [11, 14, 37], we define the 'unseen' language is a 'target' language on which a cross-lingual zero-shot prediction is done and which is different from the 'source' language on which the task-specific fine-tuning of the transformer model was performed.",
    "The three unseen test set languages-Greek, Georgian, and Spanish-allow us to evaluate the zero-shot cross-lingual transfer learning capabilities of the training techniques trained in the first, fully multilingual, setting."
  ]
}